 Blaqbonez Blaqbonez has announced the release date for his second studio album “Behold The Lamb.” The Chocolate City rapper announced 4th July and 6th July as the release dates for “Behold The Lamb” on Boomplay and other platforms, respectively. Taking to Twitter, he shared the album’s cover. The ten-track album includes features by Oxlade, Chike, Psycho YP, Bien (Sautisol), Khaligraph Jones and Ko-jo Cue. Blaqbonez had earlier hinted at something big in the works, tweeting, “these next few months about to be wilddd! ‘Young Preacher’ READY”
